Attributes that are completely uncorrelated with others:\ Daily Rate, Hourly Rate, Monthly Rate

Highly correlated Attributes:\ Percent Salary Hike - Performance Rating\ Job Level - Monthly income\ Years At Company - Years In Current Role - Years Since Last Promotion - Years With Current Manager\ Total Working Years - Age - Job Level - Monthly Income - Number of Companies Worked\

We want to get rid of highly correlated attributes since they happen to effect our dataset the same.\ Of course, we don't want to lose important features while doing so.\

Another important point here is that Rate attributes such as DailyRate is not correlated with other features.\ Thus, dropping those features will help our model.

In [44]:
def evaluate_preds(model_name, clf, test_train_flag): 
    
    if test_train_flag: # test
        y_true = y_test
        s_time = time.time()
        y_preds = clf.predict(X_test)
        e_time = time.time()
        duration_calculator(model_name, s_time, e_time, 0)
    else: # train
        y_true = y_train
        s_time = time.time()
        y_preds = clf.predict(X_train)
        e_time = time.time()
        duration_calculator(model_name, s_time, e_time, 1)
    
    
    
    results = f'''
Model Name: {model_name}
Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_true,y_preds)}
Precision: {precision_score(y_true,y_preds)}
Recall: {recall_score(y_true, y_preds)}
F1: {f1_score(y_true, y_preds)}
ROC AUC: {roc_auc_score(y_true, y_preds)}
    '''
    
    model_names.append(model_name)
    accuracy_values.append(accuracy_score(y_true,y_preds))
    precision_values.append(precision_score(y_true,y_preds))
    recall_values.append(recall_score(y_true, y_preds))
    f1_values.append(f1_score(y_true, y_preds))
    roc_auc_values.append(roc_auc_score(y_true, y_preds))
    
    return results

Function that returns the confusion matrix of the giving model

In [45]:
def conf_matrix(model_name, clf):
    y_true = y_test
    y_preds = clf.predict(X_test)
    
    print(model_name, "Confusion Matrix")
    cm_display = metrics.ConfusionMatrixDisplay(confusion_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_preds), display_labels = [False, True])
    cm_display.plot()
    plt.show()

List and function initialization for the calculation of the durations

In [46]:
train_durations = list()
test_durations = list()
In [47]:
def duration_calculator(model_name, start_time, end_time, dtype):
    diff = end_time - start_time
    print(f"The Training Duration for {model_name} Model is {diff} seconds.")
    train_durations.append(diff) if dtype else test_durations.append(diff)

def get_feature_importance(clf, feature_names):
    
    print(len(clf.coef_[0]))
    print(len(feature_names))
    
    feature_importance = (
        pd.DataFrame(
            {
                'variable': feature_names,
                'coefficient': clf.coef_[0]
            }
        )
        .round(decimals=2) \
        .sort_values('coefficient', ascending=False) \
        .style.bar(color=['red', 'green'], align='zero')
    )
    return feature_importance
